WEBVTT

00:00.160 --> 00:04.560
The resistance room testifies the war and the efforts of the Albanian people after

00:04.560 --> 00:10.960
Skanderbeg's death. At this time Lek Du Kajini was the military leader who for 11 years in a

00:10.960 --> 00:17.840
row withstand the attacks of the Ottoman army. The falling of the Škodra fortress in 1479

00:17.840 --> 00:21.840
marks also the Albanian invasion which was accompanied by many murdering and

00:21.840 --> 00:28.480
destructions across the country. Around 200,000 Albanians who could not endure the Ottoman

00:28.480 --> 00:33.360
violence were forced to immigrate to South Italy, the Arboresh, where they have preserved the

00:33.360 --> 00:39.680
language, culture and Albanian tradition. Through the exhibited documents in the glass cases of

00:39.680 --> 00:45.440
this room is testified that Skanderbeg was not only a military strategist but also a politician

00:45.440 --> 00:51.600
and diplomat of the time. He had diplomatic relations with European countries like France,

00:51.680 --> 00:55.280
Germany, Austria, Spain, Italy, Greece, etc.

00:56.320 --> 01:02.560
Janos Unjadi a Hungarian hero and Alfons V, the king of Naples were the two best allies of

01:02.560 --> 01:09.280
Skanderbeg in the anti-Ottoman war. Also, here we have recognitions of Skanderbeg from other

01:09.280 --> 01:15.600
personalities of the same time. There have been over 1,000 different books written about Skanderbeg

01:15.600 --> 01:22.400
in 73 countries across the world in 25 languages. The map across shows the countries where

01:22.400 --> 01:28.560
publications about Skanderbeg are found. The first publication about Skanderbeg refers from

01:28.560 --> 01:35.120
the years 1508 to 1510 to History of Skanderbeg by the author Marin Barleti in Latin.

01:36.080 --> 01:44.160
Gjergjari Uniti, his father-in-law, leader of Albanian's uprisings, in 1432 until 1435.

01:45.280 --> 01:50.240
Vrana Conti, commander of Kruria Fortress in its first siege, in 1450.

01:51.360 --> 01:56.560
Mimitsa Castrioti, hero's little sister, commander of Petrol Fortress near Tirana.

01:57.520 --> 02:05.040
Tanushtopia, commander of Kruria Castle in its second and third siege, in 1466 and in 1467.

02:06.160 --> 02:11.920
Lekdu Kajini is the leader of the Albanian army for 11 years in a row after Skanderbeg's death.

02:13.040 --> 02:18.880
Pal Kuka, Skanderbeg's diplomat. Zahariya Gropa, Skanderbeg's diplomat.

02:20.080 --> 02:25.760
Gjergj Leshi the warrior that killed Balaban Pasha in Kruria's second siege in 1466.

02:26.560 --> 02:27.360
you

